<h2>Solar Incentives in Pittsburgh</h2>
<p>Pittsburgh residents can take advantage of substantial solar incentives that significantly reduce installation costs. The federal solar Investment Tax Credit (ITC) provides a 30% tax credit on the total system cost, including equipment and installation, through 2032. This credit steps down to 26% in 2033 and 22% in 2034 before expiring for residential installations. Pennsylvania offers additional support through net metering policies that allow Duquesne Light customers to receive retail rate credits for excess solar energy fed back into the grid. While Pennsylvania doesn't currently offer statewide solar rebates, some local programs and utility-specific incentives may be available. Property tax exemptions for solar installations mean the added home value from solar panels won't increase your property taxes, and solar equipment is exempt from Pennsylvania's 6% sales tax.</p>

